    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Personal Health column in Science Times on Tuesday, about weight-loss products, included an outdated reference to the drug Alli, known clinically as orlistat. The Food and Drug Administration approved it on Feb. 7 for over-the-counter sale; its approval is no longer conditional.</p>
